name: Apache: La vida de Carlos Tevez
original_name: Apache: La vida de Carlos Tevez
overview: This gritty dramatization of the life of Carlos Tevez shows his rise to soccer stardom amid the harrowing conditions in Argentina's Fuerte Apache.

episodes.overview: Carlos Martínez is born in 1984. That same year, an accident involving his mother marks the beginning of a journey full of scars.

episodes.name: Through Lead and Disappointment
episodes.overview: Carlitos, already entering adolescence, does not give up despite his frustrations. The family goes through a hard time because of Kiru.

episodes.name: The Legacy
episodes.overview: Segundo's efforts pay off and everything seems to improve for the Tevez family, but the difficulties never end. Carlitos arrives at a crossroads.

episodes.name: A New World, the Origin
episodes.overview: Carlitos arrives at Boca with the support of his family. During a game he makes a move that defines his nickname and character.

episodes.name: The Value of Identity
episodes.overview: Carlitos has problems with his last name, but he doesn't want to hurt Fabiana, and a kick on the field puts his career at risk.

episodes.name: Two Mothers, One Act of Love
episodes.overview: Adriana approaches her sister and Fabiana makes a noble gesture. Carlitos resorts to alternative therapy. Danilo is caught up in a puzzling incident.

episodes.name: Two Sides of the Same Coin
episodes.overview: El Fuerte has another boss and the blood keeps flowing. Carlitos skips the AFA's pre-match preparation to go to a friend's birthday party.

episodes.name: The Big Day
episodes.overview: While Danilo is consumed by drugs and revenge, Carlitos approaches La Bombonera, which roars in anticipation of its next idol, and meets a girl.
